abstract: President Donald Trump berated FBI Director Christopher Wray on Tuesday after a U.S. government investigation found no evidence of political bias when the FBI began investigating contacts between Trump's presidential campaign and Russia in 2016.
snippet: President Donald Trump berated FBI Director Christopher Wray on Tuesday after a U.S. government investigation found no evidence of political bias when the FBI began investigating contacts between Trump's presidential campaign and Russia in 2016.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump berated FBI Director Christopher Wray on Tuesday after a U.S. government investigation found no evidence of political bias when the FBI began investigating contacts between Trump's presidential campaign and Russia in 2016.
headline_main: Trump Assails FBI Director Wray After Report Finds No Evidence of Political Bias
headline_print_headline: Trump Assails FBI Director Wray After Report Finds No Evidence of Political Bias

abstract: A future U.S. government will have to rebuild relations with China to revive international efforts to combat climate change, former New York mayor Michael Bloomberg, who is running for president, said on Tuesday.
snippet: A future U.S. government will have to rebuild relations with China to revive international efforts to combat climate change, former New York mayor Michael Bloomberg, who is running for president, said on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: MADRID — A future U.S. government will have to rebuild relations with China to revive international efforts to combat climate change, former New York mayor Michael Bloomberg, who is running for president, said on Tuesday.
headline_main: U.S. Must Fix Relations With China to Combat Climate Change-Michael Bloomberg
headline_print_headline: U.S. Must Fix Relations With China to Combat Climate Change-Michael Bloomberg

abstract: Social Democrat Sanna Marin said on Tuesday she would restore stability to Finland and keep using social media - but with care - after being sworn in as the world's youngest prime minister at the helm of a government led by women.
snippet: Social Democrat Sanna Marin said on Tuesday she would restore stability to Finland and keep using social media - but with care - after being sworn in as the world's youngest prime minister at the helm of a government led by women.
lead_paragraph: HELSINKI — Social Democrat Sanna Marin said on Tuesday she would restore stability to Finland and keep using social media - but with care - after being sworn in as the world's youngest prime minister at the helm of a government led by women.
headline_main: Finland's Young PM Promises Stability, and to Keep Posting on Instagram
headline_print_headline: Finland's Young PM Promises Stability, and to Keep Posting on Instagram

lead_paragraph: LONDON — Boris Johnson defies political gravity.
headline_main: Rule-Breaker Boris Johnson Faces Toughest Test in Election
headline_print_headline: Rule-Breaker Boris Johnson Faces Toughest Test in Election

abstract: A senior member of Britain's opposition Labour Party has dismissed the chances of the party winning power in Thursday's general election, speaking in a private conversation leaked to the Guido Fawkes news website.
snippet: A senior member of Britain's opposition Labour Party has dismissed the chances of the party winning power in Thursday's general election, speaking in a private conversation leaked to the Guido Fawkes news website.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — A senior member of Britain's opposition Labour Party has dismissed the chances of the party winning power in Thursday's general election, speaking in a private conversation leaked to the Guido Fawkes news website.
headline_main: Labour Will Not Win UK Election, Says Senior Labour Figure in Leaked Recording
headline_print_headline: Labour Will Not Win UK Election, Says Senior Labour Figure in Leaked Recording

abstract: From a denim plant in rural Georgia to a St. Paul, Minneapolis loudspeaker maker, nagging uncertainty over when President Donald Trump's trade wars might end, if ever, is confounding many U.S. manufacturers.
snippet: From a denim plant in rural Georgia to a St. Paul, Minneapolis loudspeaker maker, nagging uncertainty over when President Donald Trump's trade wars might end, if ever, is confounding many U.S. manufacturers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — From a denim plant in rural Georgia to a St. Paul, Minneapolis loudspeaker maker, nagging uncertainty over when President Donald Trump's trade wars might end, if ever, is confounding many U.S. manufacturers.
headline_main: Drowning in Uncertainty: Trade Questions Slow Investment, Squeeze Profits Across U.S.
headline_print_headline: Drowning in Uncertainty: Trade Questions Slow Investment, Squeeze Profits Across U.S.

abstract: She is taking on Pete Buttigieg directly, whacking at Mike Bloomberg and emphasizing her gender as the top woman left in the race.
snippet: She is taking on Pete Buttigieg directly, whacking at Mike Bloomberg and emphasizing her gender as the top woman left in the race.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — Faced with questions about her viability in a general election and ceding ground to opponents in the primary, Senator Elizabeth Warren is abandoning her above-the-fray approach and delivering her most forceful and direct criticism yet of her Democratic opponents.

headline_main: Elizabeth Warren Seeks a Second Act After Slip From the Top
headline_print_headline: After Slipping in the Race, Warren Goes on the Offensive

abstract: How Americans learned to live with endless wars.
snippet: How Americans learned to live with endless wars.
lead_paragraph: In fighting successfully to publish documents showing that United States officialdom has been telling lies for years about our military endeavors in Afghanistan, The Washington Post has shown how little has changed since the Vietnam era — and yet also how much more sustainable, strangely, our own era’s quagmires seem to be.
